    "title": "Concision (Medium)",
    "body": "Good writing says it once. Eliminate redundancy (repeating the same idea in different words) and wordy filler. The best choice is usually the shortest one that keeps the full meaning and stays grammatical.",
    "key_points": [
      "Cut words that repeat an idea.",
      "Prefer the shortest clear, grammatical option.",
      "Don't delete meaning — only redundancy."
    ]
  },
